[3m[2m@synopsis{Compare two location values lexicographically.}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
When the two locations refer to different files, their paths are compared as string.
When they refer to the same file, their offsets are compared when present.
}[0m
[3m[2m@pitfalls{
This ordering regards the location value itself as opposed to the text it refers to.
}[0m
[1mbool[0m isLexicallyLess([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r)
    = isSameFile(l, r) ? (l.offset ? 0) < (r.offset ? 0) : l.top < r.top;

[3m[2m@synopsis{Get the textual content a location refers to.}[0m
[1mstr[0m getContent([1mloc[0m l) = readFile(l);

[3m[2m@synopsis{Is a location textually (strictly) contained in another location?}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
Strict containment between two locations `inner` and `outer` holds when


- `outer` 's text begins before `inner` 's text, or
- `outer` 's text ends after `inner` 's text, or
- both.
}[0m
[3m[2m@javaClass{org.rascalmpl.library.Prelude}[0m
[1mjava[0m [1mbool[0m isStrictlyContainedIn([1mloc[0m inner, [1mloc[0m outer);

[3m[2m@synopsis{Is a location textually contained in another location?}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
Containment between two locations `inner` and `outer` holds when


- `inner` and `outer` are equal, or
- `inner` is strictly contained in `outer`.
}[0m
[3m[2m@javaClass{org.rascalmpl.library.Prelude}[0m
[1mjava[0m [1mbool[0m isContainedIn([1mloc[0m inner, [1mloc[0m outer);

[3m[2m@synopsis{Begins a location's text before (but may overlap with) another location's text?}[0m
[1mbool[0m beginsBefore([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r) = isSameFile(l, r) && l.offset < r.offset;

[3m[2m@synopsis{Begins and ends a location's text before another location's text?}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
`isBefore(l, r)` holds when `l` 's text occurs textually before `r` 's text.
}[0m
[1mbool[0m isBefore([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r) = isSameFile(l, r) && l.offset + l.length <= r.offset;

[3m[2m@synopsis{Occurs a location's text _immediately_ before another location's text?}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
`isImmediatelyBefore(l, r)` holds when `l` 's text occurs textually before, and is adjacent to, `r` 's text.
}[0m
[1mbool[0m isImmediatelyBefore([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r)
    = isSameFile(l, r) && l.offset + l.length == r.offset;

[3m[2m@synopsis{Begins a location's text after (but may overlap with) another location's text?

Description
`beginsAfter(l, r)` holds when `l` 's text begins after `r` 's text. No assumption is made about the end of both texts.
In other words, `l` 's text may end before or after the end of `r` 's text.}[0m
[1mbool[0m beginsAfter([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r) = isSameFile(l, r) && l.offset > r.offset;

[3m[2m@synopsis{Is a location's text completely after another location's text?}[0m
[1mbool[0m isAfter([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r) = isBefore(r, l);

[3m[2m@synopsis{Is a location's text _immediately_ after another location's text?}[0m
[1mbool[0m isImmediatelyAfter([1mloc[0m l, [1mloc[0m r) = isImmediatelyBefore(r, l);

