    = changed(l.top, edits);

[3m[2m@synopsis{String rewriting operations}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
The core operation is to replace a substring with another.
The replace operator uses a `loc` value to point to a range inside a string,
and a `str` as its replacement.
}[0m
[3m[2m@benefits{
* backends have to implement only one ((TextEdit)) operation to be complete.
* use the ((delete)), ((insertBefore)) and ((insertAfter)) "macros" for convenience and brevity.
}[0m
[1mdata[0m TextEdit = replace([1mloc[0m range, [1mstr[0m replacement);

[3m[2m@synopsis{Deletion is replacement with an empty string.}[0m
TextEdit delete([1mloc[0m range) = replace(range, "");

[3m[2m@synopsis{Inserting before a given range.}[0m
[3m[2m@benefits{
