[3m[2m@synopsis{Provides access to the JDK javac compiler, to compile (generated) Java code.}[0m
[3m[2m@benefits{
* Compile any Java code, stored anywhere reachable through a `loc` and using any library
reachable through a `loc`, to JVM bytecode using the standard JDK compiler.
}[0m
[3m[2m@pitfalls{
* If you are looking for Java analysis and transformation support in Rascal please go find
the [java-air](http://www.rascalmpl.org/docs/Packages/RascalAir) package. The current module
only provides a Java to bytecode compilation API. 
}[0m
[1mmodule[0m lang::java::Compiler

[1mextend[0m Message;

[1mimport[0m IO;
[1mimport[0m Location;
[1mimport[0m String;
[1mimport[0m util::FileSystem;
[1mimport[0m util::PathConfig;
[1mimport[0m util::Reflective;
[1mimport[0m util::UUID;

[3m[2m@synopsis{Compile all the .java files in source folders in PathConfig}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
See ((compileJavaSourceFolders)) for more information.
}[0m
[1mlist[0m[Message] compileJava(PathConfig pcfg)
    = compileJavaSourceFolders(pcfg.srcs, pcfg.bin, libs = pcfg.libs);

[3m[2m@synopsis{Compile a single Java source file}[0m
[3m[2m@pitfalls{
* `file` has to be reachable from `srcs`, because a fully qualified class name is computing by relativizing the source file `loc` against the `srcs` folders.
* The source files is read using ((readFile)).
* All class files, which could be many in the case of anonymous or nested classes, are written directly to the `bin` folder.
* `libs` is typically a list of `jar+file:///` or `mvn:///` locations, one for each (transitive) compile-time dependency.
Without these the compiler will complain about missing symbols and return error messages.
}[0m
[1mlist[0m[Message] compileJavaSourceFile(
    [1mloc[0m file,
    [1mloc[0m bin,
    [1mlist[0m[[1mloc[0m] srcs,
    [1mlist[0m[[1mloc[0m] libs = []
)
    = compileJava(
          {<file, qualifiedName(file, srcs), readFile(file) >}, bin, libs = libs
      );

[3m[2m@synopsis{Compile all java source files from a list of source folders.}[0m
[3m[2m@description{
* Qualified class names are obtained by relativizing against the source folders.
* Source code is read in using ((readFile)).
* Bytecode files are written directly into the `bin` folder
}[0m
[1mlist[0m[Message] compileJavaSourceFolders(
    [1mlist[0m[[1mloc[0m] srcFolders,
    [1mloc[0m bin,
    [1mlist[0m[[1mloc[0m] libs = []
)
    = compileJava(
          {<f, qualifiedName(f, srcFolders), readFile(f)>
          | src <- srcFolders, f <- find(src, "java")
          }, bin,
          libs = libs
      );

