[3m[2m// TIL; apparently before the year 1752 the US was still on the Julian calendar which calculated a leap year every 4 years. The algorithm used here only works for the Gregorian calendar[0m
[3m[2m// Increment a date by a day according to the Gregorian calendar algorithm for leap year calculation[0m
[1mdatetime[0m incDateByOneDay([1mdatetime[0m dt) {
    [1mif[0m (dt.day < 28) {
        [1mreturn[0m createDate(dt.year, dt.month, dt.day + 1);
