[3m[2m@synopsis{Starts the Z3 solver.
	To run the solver the path to Z3 needs to be configure either by adding the `-Dsolver.z3.path=<local.path.to.z3>` to your eclipse.ini configuration or by supplying it 
	when you call the solver using the keyword parameter 'pathToZ3'}[0m
PID startZ3([1mstr[0m pathToZ3 = getSystemProperty("solver.z3.path")) {
    pid = createProcess("<pathToZ3>/bin/z3", args = ["-smt2", "-in"]);
    
    [3m[2m// The print-success option is needed so that each entered statement returns a result. This way we have a predictable inputstream that we can read[0m
