[3m[2m@synopsis{Visualizing values using "ASCII art".}[0m
[3m[2m@synopsis{This module provides functions that map values to strings using ASCII Art pretty printing.

The words [ASCII Art](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASCII_art) refers to the technique of 
constructing images from text characters that are in the ASCII set. However, in this case
we may use any Unicode character for visual representation purposes.}[0m
[3m[2m@examples{
```rascal-shell
syntax E = "e" | E "+" E;
import IO;
import vis::Text;
ex = prettyTree([E] "e+e+e");
println(ex);
```
}[0m
